### ── PAYMENT SERVICE (/payments) ───────────────────────────────────────────
### Environment: Ctrl+Shift+P → Rest Client: Switch Environment → dev
### Flow: createOrder (sales.http) → initiatePayment → capturePayment → refundPayment
### Admin/Manager: capturePayment, failPayment (PSP simulation)

### 1. Initiate payment — Customer Bauer
### orderId: replace with ID returned from createOrder in sales.http
# @name initPayment
POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/initiatePayment
Authorization: {{customerBauerAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "REPLACE_WITH_ORDER_ID",
  "provider": "StripeDE",
  "idempotencyKey": "pay-test-001",
  "amount": 38900.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### 2. Same idempotencyKey again — should return same session (no new record created)
POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/initiatePayment
Authorization: {{customerBauerAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "REPLACE_WITH_ORDER_ID",
  "provider": "StripeDE",
  "idempotencyKey": "pay-test-001",
  "amount": 38900.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### 3. Capture payment — Admin (PSP simulation)
### paymentId: replace with ID returned from step 1
POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/capturePayment
Authorization: {{adminAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "paymentId": "REPLACE_WITH_PAYMENT_ID",
  "transactionReference": "TXN-STRIPE-001"
}

### 4. Query payment status — Customer
GET {{baseUrl}}/payments/getPaymentStatus(orderId='REPLACE_WITH_ORDER_ID')
Authorization: {{customerBauerAuth}}

### 5. List payments — Admin
GET {{baseUrl}}/payments/Payments
Authorization: {{adminAuth}}

### 6. Initiate refund — Admin (from CAPTURED status)
POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/refundPayment
Authorization: {{adminAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "paymentId": "REPLACE_WITH_PAYMENT_ID"
}

### 7. Fail payment — Admin (on a new payment)
POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/failPayment
Authorization: {{adminAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "paymentId": "REPLACE_WITH_PAYMENT_ID"
}

### 8. Retry after failed payment — Customer
POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/retryPayment
Authorization: {{customerBauerAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "REPLACE_WITH_ORDER_ID",
  "idempotencyKey": "pay-test-002"
}

### 9. Query another customer's payment status — should be rejected
GET {{baseUrl}}/payments/getPaymentStatus(orderId='REPLACE_WITH_ORDER_ID')
Authorization: {{customerHoffmannAuth}}
